com.nexmo.client

Enum NexmoConnectionState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<NexmoConnectionState>
      • com.nexmo.client.NexmoConnectionState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<NexmoConnectionState>

    public enum NexmoConnectionState
extends java.lang.Enum<NexmoConnectionState>
    An enum to represent the connection status for a NexmoConnectionListener.

    CONNECTED - connection completion

    DISCONNECTED - NexmoUser has been disconnected. Possible cause may be connectivity issues. * Also occurs after an explicit NexmoClient.logout().

    RECONNECTED - the connection is reconnected

    CONNECTING - in the process of connecting

    RECONNECTING - in the process of reconnecting

    CONNECT_TIMEOUT - the connection failed due to a timeout

    CONNECT_ERROR - the connection failed due to an error

    RECONNECT_ERROR - the reconnection failed due to an error

     used by:
     NexmoClient.setConnectionListener(NexmoConnectionListener)
